                            <comment id="16815912" author="nite" created="Fri, 12 Apr 2019 02:53:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since maven.compiler.release overrides maven.compiler.source, and&#160;&apos;&#8211;release&apos; overrides &apos;-source&apos; in javac, it seems logical to default &apos;source&apos; to the same value as &apos;release&apos;. It certainly fixes the issue in local testing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16816925" author="nite" created="Sat, 13 Apr 2019 12:13:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems to work with 3.1.1-SNAPSHOT.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16816930" author="rfscholte" created="Sat, 13 Apr 2019 12:39:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t recognize any commits since 3.1.0 related to this. Shall I close this as &apos;can&apos;t reproduce&apos;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16816940" author="nite" created="Sat, 13 Apr 2019 13:23:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah, right, it was just my local repo that got a candidate fix and there&apos;s no 3.1.1-SNAPSHOT in &lt;a href=&quot;http://repository.apache.org/snapshots/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://repository.apache.org/snapshots/&lt;/a&gt; and I did not notice &apos;mvn -U&apos; did not clear out my local version.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A candidate fix is here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-javadoc-plugin/pull/25&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/maven-javadoc-plugin/pull/25&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16816948" author="rfscholte" created="Sat, 13 Apr 2019 13:45:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This shouldn&apos;t be required. There&apos;s a new property since 3.1.0 called &lt;a href=&quot;https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-javadoc-plugin/javadoc-mojo.html#release&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;release&lt;/a&gt; (I just noticed the wrong @since value is used...) which already defaults to &lt;tt&gt;maven.compiler.release&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="16816961" author="nite" created="Sat, 13 Apr 2019 14:28:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, I noticed that property. I agree, that was just the first cut before I opened the project in an IDE &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; The pull request is updated with a more correct solution.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16816965" author="rfscholte" created="Sat, 13 Apr 2019 14:37:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, that change makes sense.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
